orld%2C%20higher%20than%20even%20South%20Africa%2C%20Brazil%20and%20US.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20%E2%80%98billionaire%20raj%E2%80%99%20(a%20term%20used%20to%20define%20the%20post-2010s%20rapid%20rise%20of%20billionaires%20in%20the%20country%2C%20at%20odds%20with%20lives%20of%20millions%2C%20popularised%20by%20James%20Crabtree%E2%80%99s%20book%20of%20the%20same%20name)%20is%20now%20more%20unequal%20than%20the%20British%20colonial%20raj%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20two%20other%20observations%2C%20one%20on%20income%20tax%20being%20regressive%2C%20if%20seen%20from%20the%20prism%20of%20net%20wealth%20in%20society.%20Also%2C%20the%20poor%20economic%20data%2C%20which%20has%20%E2%80%9Cseen%20a%20decline%20recently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20finds%20that%20while%20inequality%20has%20been%20rising%20sharply%20in%20India%20since%20the%201980s%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbetween%202014-15%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%C2%A0rise%20of%20top-end%20inequality%20has%20been%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20terms%20of%20wealth%20concentration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20listed%20five%20%E2%80%9CKey%20findings%E2%80%9D%20as%20follows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C1.%20Inequality%20declined%20post-independence%20till%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20after%20which%20it%20began%20rising%20and%20has%20skyrocketed%20since%20the%20early%202000s.%20Trends%20of%20top%20income%20and%20wealth%20shares%20track%20each%20other%20over%20the%20entire%20period%20of%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Between%202014-15%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20top-end%20inequality%20has%20been%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20terms%20of%20wealth%20concentration.%20By%202022-23%2C%20top%201%25%20income%20and%20wealth%20shares%20(22.6%25%20and%2040.1%25)%20are%20at%20their%20highest%20historical%20levels%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%201%25%20income%20share%20is%20among%20the%20very%20highest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20higher%20than%20even%20South%20Africa%2C%20Brazil%20and%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20In%20line%20with%20earlier%20work%2C%20the%20paper%20finds%20suggestive%20evidence%20that%20the%20Indian%20income%20tax%20system%20might%20be%20regressive%20when%20viewed%20from%20the%20lens%20of%20net%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20A%20restructuring%20of%20the%20tax%20code%20to%20account%20for%20both%20income%20and%20wealth%2C%20and%20broad-based%20public%20investments%20in%20health%2C%20education%20and%20nutrition%20are%20needed%20to%20enable%20the%20average%20Indian%2C%20and%20not%20just%20the%20elites%2C%20to%20meaningfully%20benefit%20from%20the%20ongoing%20wave%20of%20globalization.%20Besides%20serving%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20fight%20inequality%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Csuper%20tax%E2%80%9D%20of%202%25%20on%20the%20net%20wealth%20of%20the%20167%20wealthiest%20families%20in%202022-23%20would%20yield%200.5%25%20of%20national%20income%20in%20revenues%20and%20create%20valuable%20fiscal%20space%20to%20facilitate%20such%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20paper%20emphasises%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20economic%20data%20in%20India%20is%20notably%20poor%20and%20has%20seen%20a%20decline%20recently.%20It%20is%20therefore%20likely%20that%20these%20new%20estimates%20represent%20a%20lower%20bound%20to%20actual%20inequality%20levels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20512px)%2085vw%2C%20512px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j.png%20512w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j-300x231.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702452%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20World%20Inequality%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20are%20Nitin%20Kumar%20Bharti%2C%20Lucas%20Chancel%2C%20Thomas%20Piketty%2C%20and%20Anmol%20Somanchi%20who%20have%20pulled%20together%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20income%20accounts%2C%20wealth%20aggregates%2C%20tax%20tabulations%2C%20rich%20lists%2C%20and%20surveys%20on%20income%2C%20consumption%2C%20and%20wealth%20in%20a%20consistent%20framework%20to%20present%20long%20run%20homogeneous%20series%20of%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20India%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20has%20been%20adept%20at%20refuting%20any%20global%20assessments%20pointing%20to%20economic%20facts%20such%20as%20hunger%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20while%20not%20having%20made%20data%20available%20at%20regular%20intervals%20as%20was%20the%20case%20earlier.%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20data%20itself%20is%20highly%20contested.%20Former%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fgdp-numbers-are-mystifying-dont-add-up-former-cea-arvind-subramanian%23%3A~%3Atext%3Deconomy-%2C%2527GDP%2520Numbers%2520Are%2520Mystifying%252C%2520Don%2527t%2520Add%2520Up%2527%2C5%2525%252C%2527%2520he%2520said.%5C%22%3Ehas%20expressed%20surprise%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20how%20the%20GDP%20has%20been%20said%20to%20be%20rising.%20India%20has%20missed%20its%20date%20for%20the%20decadal%20census%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20140%20years%2C%20in%202021%2C%20citing%20COVID-19.%20India%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-is-disputing-indias-covid-death-numbers-so-govt-wants-to-bury-global-report%5C%22%3Ehas%20issues%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20WHO%20data%20on%20underestimation%20of%20the%20Covid%20death%20toll%20by%20ten%20times.%20It%20is%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20which%20contests%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20Covid%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710915070000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13093230%2Fkarthik-chandran-uwSbfD1afxI-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Findias-inequality-at-historic-high-wealth-concentration-shot-up-sharpest-between-2014-5-and-2022-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Data%20on%20India%20for%20a%20century%20has%20revealed%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%20now%20as%20being%20worse%20than%20during%20British%20colonial%20rule%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Inequality%20Lab.%20Using%20%E2%80%9Cbillionaire%20raj%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20present%20times%2C%20research%20has%20found%20that%20inequality%20declined%20post-independence%20till%20the%201980s%2C%20rose%20afterwards%20and%20is%20%E2%80%9Cskyrocketing%20now%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Findias-inequality-at-historic-high-wealth-concentration-shot-up-sharpest-between-2014-5-and-2022-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%2025%2C%20he%20decided%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20stuck%20in%20a%20job%20forever.%20Here's%20how%20he%20was%20able%20to%20retire%20by%2036.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yaron%20Goldstein%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f8f24e4af076d3cf918807%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222604%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYaron%20Goldstein%20retired%20at%2036%20years%20old%20after%20working%20at%20BCG%2C%20Google%20and%20Meta.%3Cp%3EYaron%20Goldstein%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYaron%20Goldstein%20achieved%20financial%20independence%20at%20the%20age%20of%2036.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoldstein's%20strategy%20included%20mindful%20spending%20and%20investing%20a%20big%20portion%20of%20his%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20follows%20the%204%25%20rule%2C%20which%20is%20common%20in%20the%20FIRE%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fgoldsteiny%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYaron%20Goldstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%2025%20when%20he%20decided%20to%20start%20working%20toward%20financial%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldstein%20was%20working%20toward%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20computational%20and%20advanced%20mathematics%20in%20Berlin%2C%20his%20hometown.%20While%20on%20a%20research%20internship%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%202010%2C%20he%20connected%20with%20a%20Wall%20Street%20investment%20advisor%20who%20would%20become%20his%20unofficial%20mentor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20mentor%20gave%20him%20a%20list%20of%20what%20he%20considered%20%26quot%3Brequired%20reading.%26quot%3B%20The%20list%20included%20Tim%20Ferriss'%20%26quot%3B4%20Hour%20Workweek%26quot%3B%20and%20Malcolm%20Gladwell's%20%26quot%3BOutliers.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20his%20readings%2C%20Goldstein%20started%20to%20think%20about%20how%20happiness%20and%20money%20are%20related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20guy%20is%20making%20quite%20a%20good%20case%20for%3A%20Maybe%2040%20years%20from%20now%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20the%20guy%20who%20focuses%20his%20whole%20life%20on%20doing%20a%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20about%20his%20reaction%20to%20reading%20Ferriss'%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvesting%20early%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20Goldstein%20went%20on%20to%20work%20at%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta.%20His%20career%20took%20him%20from%20Tel%20Aviv%20and%20Zurich%20to%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20his%20career%20spanned%20continents%20and%20big-name%20companies%2C%20his%20ultimate%20goal%20was%20to%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20money%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestment-wise%2C%20he%20started%20off%20small.%20When%20he%20got%20his%20first%20job%20as%20a%20post-doctoral%20student%20at%20a%20university%20in%20Berlin%2C%20he%20started%20putting%20away%20a%20few%20hundred%20euros%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldstein's%20first%20job%20out%20of%20academia%20was%20working%20for%20BCG%20in%20Berlin.%20He%20increased%20his%20contributions%20to%20between%201%2C000%20and%201%2C500%20euros%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202017%2C%20four%20years%20after%20he%20set%20off%20on%20his%20financial%20independence%20journey%2C%20Goldstein%20devised%20a%20rough%20goal%20for%20his%20retirement%20years%3A%20He%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20stable%2C%20risk-free%20income%20of%205%2C000%20euros%20a%20month%20to%20live%20off%20of%20during%20his%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20lived%20on%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20his%20income%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20his%20career%20and%20later%20cut%20his%20expenses%20to%20about%2050%25%20of%20his%20income.%20He%20saved%20all%20his%20annual%20bonuses%20and%20stocks%20that%20were%20part%20of%20his%20salary.%20Goldstein%20kept%20about%2010%2C000%20euros%20in%20a%20bank%20account%20and%20invested%20everything%20else%20in%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMindful%20purchasing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20seven%20years%20of%20starting%20his%20career%20as%20a%20data%20scientist%2C%20Goldstein%20more%20than%20doubled%20his%20salary.%20By%202020%2C%20he%20was%20making%20about%20330%2C000%20euros.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20his%20salary%20rose%2C%20he%20put%20more%20money%20toward%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20mindset%20that%20helped%20him%20came%20down%20to%20evaluating%20what%20gave%20him%20happiness%20and%20avoiding%20lifestyle%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20any%20purchases%2C%20he%20would%20ask%20himself%3A%20%26quot%3BIs%20there%20something%20else%20that%20would%20satisfy%20me%20in%20a%20similar%20way%20for%20a%20third%20of%20the%20price%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20his%20passion%20for%20green%20tea%20as%20one%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20I%20buy%20luxury%20tea%2C%20which%20is%20%2450%20per%2050%20grams%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20it's%20still%20cheaper%20than%20going%20to%20Starbucks%20every%20single%20day%20and%20getting%20coffee%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20have%20this%20much%20more%20exclusive%20thing%20in%20my%20life%20that%20gives%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20joy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20never%20bought%20a%20car%20because%20Berlin%20and%20Zurich%2C%20where%20he%20spent%20a%20big%20part%20of%20his%20career%2C%20both%20have%20strong%20public%20transportation%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20not%20have%20this%20large%20or%20potentially%20huge%20expense%2C%20and%20I%20could%20put%20that%20money%20instead%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20his%20decision%20to%20remain%20car-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldstein%20said%20luck%20also%20played%20a%20role%20in%20jumpstarting%20his%20investments.%20He%20was%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20Tesla%2C%20and%20put%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20amount%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20net%20worth%20into%20Tesla%20stock%20in%202016%2C%20which%20rallied%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20Model%20X.%20He%20said%20he%20also%20spent%20many%20years%20of%20his%20career%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20where%20taxes%20are%20very%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERetirement%20approach%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoldstein%20retired%20in%20May%202023%2C%20about%2010%20years%20after%20he%20first%20began%20earning%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20follows%20the%204%25%20rule%2C%20which%20is%20common%20in%20the%20FIRE%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%26quot%3Bfinancial%20independence%2C%20retire%20early%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20community%2C%20and%20which%20suggests%20it's%20safe%20to%20withdraw%20about%204%25%20of%20your%20total%20portfolio%20in%20each%20year%20of%20retirement.%20It%20aims%20to%20help%20retirees%20find%20a%20safe%20withdrawal%20rate%2C%20but%20should%20be%20customized%20depending%20on%20the%20number%20of%20years%20expected%20in%20retirement%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestor.vanguard.com%2Finvestor-resources-education%2Farticle%2Ffueling-the-fire-movement-updating-the-4-rule-for-early-retirees%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvesting-strategy-to-achieve-financial-independence-fire-movement-index-funds-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJamila%20Souffrant%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20set%20herself%20a%20seven-year%20retirement%20goal%20when%20she%20turned%2033%2C%20approached%20early%20retirement%20in%20a%20similar%20way.%20A%20key%20component%20of%20her%20plan%20was%20putting%20her%20money%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20realized%20that%2C%20while%20saving%20is%20good%20and%20important%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20get%20me%20to%20wealth%20or%20financial%20independence%2C%26quot%3B%20Souffrant%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20losing%20out%20by%20not%20investing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouffrant%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20have%20three%20children%2C%20set%20up%20automatic%20contributions%20from%20their%20paychecks%20to%20their%20investment%20and%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20which%20forced%20them%20to%20manage%20with%20the%20remaining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20who%20have%20reached%20FIRE%20reject%20the%204%25%20rule%2C%20saying%20it%20amounts%20to%20an%20unnecessarily%20large%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retirees-say-4-percent-rule-overrated-for-fire-retirement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELauren%20and%20Steven%20Keys%3C%2Fa%3E%20quit%20full-time%20work%20in%20their%2020s%20but%20continue%20to%20work%20on%20side%20gigs.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20idea%20of%20needing%2025%20times%20your%20annual%20expenses%20to%20feel%20like%20you%20can%20quit%20your%20full-time%20job%20became%20kind%20of%20laughable%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Steven%20previously%20told%20BI%20about%20the%204%25%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdjusted%20for%20taxes%2C%20Goldstein%20said%20he%20aims%20to%20live%20on%203%25%20of%20his%20portfolio%20per%20year%2C%20which%20he%20believes%20can%20last%20him%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%2C%20especially%20if%20he%20is%20%26quot%3Bmore%20frugal%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20early%20retirement%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20can%20ever%20force%20you%20to%20say%20success%20means%20joining%20a%20big%20company%20and%20staying%20there%20for%2040%20years%20and%20going%20up%20the%20career%20ladder%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-early-financial-independence-mindful-spending-investing-berlin-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710914707000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f8f224895d822030321d11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-early-financial-independence-mindful-spending-investing-berlin-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3B40%20years%20from%20now%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20the%20guy%20who%20focuses%20his%20whole%20life%20on%20doing%20a%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20Yaron%20Goldstein%20told%20Business%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22shubhangigoel%40insider.com%20(Shubhangi%20Goel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-early-financial-independence-mindful-spending-investing-berlin-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kerala%3A%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Lone%20Muslim%20Candidate%20%E2%80%98Sidelined%E2%80%99%20at%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Roadshow%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20111215%2FGJBaWRLWQAAmam1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20or%20CPI(M)%20accused%20Prime%20Minister%20Nare