0%E2%80%9CZangnan%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fchina-criticises-indian-ministers-visit-arunachal-pradesh-foreign-ministry-2023-04-10%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20Chinese%20name%20for%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20it%20claims%20as%20%E2%80%98South%20Tibet%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20part%20of%20Chinese%20territory.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fresponse-to-queries.htm%3Fdtl%2F37720%2FOfficial%2BSpokespersons%2Bresponse%2Bto%2Bmedia%2Bqueries%2Bon%2Bcomments%2Bmade%2Bby%2Bthe%2BSpokesperson%2Bof%2Bthe%2BChinese%2BDefence%2BMinistry%2Bregarding%2BArunachal%2BPradesh%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20external%20affairs%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20reiterated%20its%20dismissal%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20remarks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20noted%20the%20comments%20made%20by%20the%20Spokesperson%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Defence%20Ministry%20advancing%20absurd%20claims%20over%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Indian%20State%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20Repeating%20baseless%20arguments%20in%20this%20regard%20does%20not%20lend%20such%20claims%20any%20validity%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2019).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJaiswal%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CArunachal%20Pradesh%20was%2C%20is%20and%20will%20always%20be%20an%20integral%20and%20inalienable%20part%20of%20India.%20Its%20people%20will%20continue%20to%20benefit%20from%20our%20development%20programmes%20and%20infrastructure%20projects.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Chinese%20side%20had%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20current%20situation%20at%20the%20border%20was%20%E2%80%9Cstable%E2%80%9D%20but%20that%20Indian%20actions%20were%20%E2%80%9Ccontrary%20to%20the%20efforts%20of%20both%20sides%20to%20ease%20the%20border%20situation%20and%20