20the%20event%2C%20all%20schools%20were%20explicitly%20instructed%20to%20abstain%20from%20such%20practices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssistant%20Returning%20Officer%20(ARO)%20P.%20Suresh%2C%20spoke%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20confirming%20that%20these%20practices%20violate%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20(MCC).%20%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20inquiry%20is%20concluded%2C%20reports%20will%20be%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20for%20further%20action%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710862188000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19190947%2FUntitled-design-48-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcoimbatore-inquiry-ordered-over-presence-of-schoolchildren-at-pm-modis-roadshow%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Children%20under%2014%20from%20a%20government-aided%20school%20were%20seen%20donning%20saffron-coloured%20cloth%20strips%20bearing%20BJP%20symbols%2C%20at%20various%20locations%20throughout%20the%20roadshow%20on%20March%2018%2C%20performing%20on%20stages%20arranged%20by%20workers%20of%20the%20BJP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcoimbatore-inquiry-ordered-over-presence-of-schoolchildren-at-pm-modis-roadshow%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CAA%3A%20One%20More%20Tool%20in%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Arsenal%20Against%20the%20Muslim%20Community%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F12182004%2FTanushree-Bhasin-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20massive%20scam%20related%20to%20electoral%20bonds%20was%20unfolding%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20declared%20the%20rules%20and%20procedures%20for%20implementation%20of%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(CAA)%20which%20was%20passed%20nearly%20four%20years%20ago.%20The%20timing%20of%20its%20implementation%2C%20with%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scam%20coming%20to%20the%20surface%20and%20general%20elections%20right%20around%20the%20corner%2C%20is%20very%20obvious%20given%20the%20pattern%20of%20politics%20pursued%20by%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20recalls%20that%20CAA%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20fore%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizenship%20(NRC)%2C%20which%20was%20undertaken%20in%20Assam.%20The%20people%20were%20asked%20to%20provide%20the%20papers%20related%20to%20their%20citizenship.%20The%20understanding%20was%20that%20Assam%20has%20been%20infiltrated%20by%20Bangladeshi%20Muslims%20to%20the%20tune%20of%2015%20million%20and%20this%20step%20will%20help%20the%20government%20to%20expel%20them.%20They%20were%20called%20termites%2C%20detention%20centres%20came%20up%20and%20many%20more%20were%20planned%20at%20different%20places.%20The%20results%20of%20the%20NRC%20were%20surprising.%20Out%20of%20the%20around%2019%20lakh%20people%20who%20did%20not%20have%20proper%20papers%2C%20only%207%20lakh%20were%20Muslims.%20To%20bypass%20the%20issue%2C%20CAA%20was%20brought%20forward.%20The%20propaganda%20of%2015%20million%20Bangladeshi%20Muslims%20fell%20flat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20CAA%2C%20Hindus%2C%20Christians%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Buddhists%20and%20Jains%2C%20who%20came%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20before%20December%202014%2C%20were%20to%20be%20given%20citizenship.%20Interestingly%2C%20Muslims%20were%20kept%20out%20of%20this%20list.%20This%20led%20to%20strong%20protests%20all%20over%20the%20country%20and%20the%20protests%20in%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20(AMU)%20and%20Jamia%20Milia%20Islamia%20in%20particular%20were%20brutally%20crushed.%20This%20in%20turn%20led%20to%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20mass%20movements%20of%20independent%20India%20starting%20at%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Shaheen%20Bagh.%20Remarkably%2C%20these%20protests%20were%20led%20by%20Muslim%20women%20all%20over%20the%20country.%20They%20protested%20with%20the%20constitution%20in%20hand%20and%20Gandhi%20in%20their%20hearts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20Parvesh%20Sahib%20Singh%20Varma%20at%20the%20time%2C%20had%20said%20these%20protests%20were%20a%20threat%20to%20Hindus%20as%20the%20protestors%20may%20rape%20and%20kill%20them.%20Another%20BJP%20leader%2C%20Kapil%20Sharma%2C%20had%20threatened%20that%20if%20protestors%20weren%E2%80%99t%20cleared%20by%20the%20police%20then%20they%20would%20do%20it%20themselves.%20To%20cap%20it%20all%2C%20the%20then%20minister%20of%20state%2C%20Aunrag%20Thakur%2C%20gave%20the%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EGoli%20Maro%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Riots%20in%20the%20capital%20followed%20soon%20after%20%E2%80%93%2051%20people%20lost%20their%20lives%20out%20of%20which%2038%20were%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%2C%20that%20was%20in%20cold%20storage%20since%20then%2C%20has%20been%20rekindled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20are%20the%20norms%20for%20giving%20refuge%20to%20the%20persecuted%20people%20from%20neighbouring%20countries%3F%20Indira%20Jaisingh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Findira-jasing-caa-rules-against-equality-federalism-constitution-9210384%2F%5C%22%3Epoints%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CThe%20constitution%20confers%20citizenship%20by%20birth%2C%20descent%20and%20migration%2C%20regardless%20of%20religion%E2%80%A6The%20Citizenship%20Act%20(1955)%20was%20enacted%20by%20Parliament%20to%20regularise%20the%20grant%20and%20termination%20of%20citizenship.%20The%201955%20act%20also%20does%20not%20make%20religion%20a%20criterion%20for%20granting%20citizenship.%20With%20the%20amendment%20of%20rules%2C%20citizenship%20will%20be%20granted%20by%20naturalisation%20based%20on%20religion%20alone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20this%20amendment%20violates%20Article%2014%20which%20ensures%20equality%20before%20law%20and%20equal%20protection%2C%20irrespective%20of%20religion.%20Article%2014%20applies%20to%20all%20persons%2C%20not%20just%20citizens.%20The%20CAA%20denies%20fast-track%20citizenship%20to%20Muslims.%20It%20also%20excludes%20people%20from%20countries%20other%20than%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Bangladesh.%20That%20the%20Ahmadiyya%20Muslims%20in%20Pakistan%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20persecuted%20minorities%20is%20well%20known%2C%20but%20the%20CAA%20is%20silent%20on%20them%20because%20of%20the%20religious%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Funderstanding-caa-rules-the-process-and-what-it-means-to-resist%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20CAA%20Rules%2C%20the%20Process%2C%20and%20What%20It%20Means%20to%20Resist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20argued%20that%20the%20CAA%20was%20enacted%20to%20provide%20fast-track%20citizenship%20to%20persecuted%20minorities%20in%20neighbouring%20countries.%20Yet%2C%20the%20statute%20or%20rules%20of%20the%20Act%20do%20not%20mention%20persecution%20and%20proof%20of%20persecution%20is%20not%20required%20before%20citizenship%20is%20granted.%20Under%20the%20CAA%20rules%2C%20immigrants%20from%20the%20three%20countries%20need%20only%20prove%20their%20religion%2C%20date%20of%20entry%20to%20Indian%20and%20country%20of%20origin%20and%20knowledge%20of%20an%20Indian%20language.%20The%20rules%20regarding%20proof%20of%20country%20of%20origin%20have%20been%20considerably%20relaxed.%20The%20earlier%20requirement%20of%20a%20valid%20residential%20permit%20from%20India%20and%20a%20valid%20passport%20issued%20by%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Bangladesh%20has%20been%20eliminated.%20The%20proof%20of%20persecution%20has%20been%20waived%20and%20the%20process%20has%20been%20fast-tracked%2C%20cutting%20it%20down%20to%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20asserted%20that%20Hindus%20in%20these%20countries%20can%20only%20turn%20to%20India%20while%20Muslims%20can%20go%20to%20any%20country%20that%20follows%20Islam.%20This%20logic%20is%20flawed.%20It%20is%20well%20known%20that%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20apart%20from%20minority%20communities%20like%20Hindus%20and%20Christians%2C%20the%20Ahmadiays%20and%20Kadiyanis%20have%20to%20face%20persecution.%20When%20we%20talk%20of%20giving%20refuge%20to%20the%20persecuted%20communities%2C%20our%20humane%20values%20have%20to%20come%20to%20the%20fore.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20largest%20persecuted%20groups%20in%20recent%20times%20have%20been%20Hindus%20(Tamils)%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20Rohingyas%20in%20Myanmar.%20Why%20have%20they%20been%20left%20out%20from%20the%20list%20of%20those%20who%20will%20be%20given%20citizenship%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20organisations%20and%20individuals%20have%20challenged%20CAA%20on%20different%20grounds%20since%20its%20introduction.%20These%20pleas%20are%20pending%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3B%20an%20early%20resolution%20of%20this%20vexed%20issue%20is%20more%20than%20overdue%20and%20hopefully%20will%20come%20up%20for%20hearing%20soon.%20It%20is%20very%20clear%20that%20BJP%20is%20raking%20it%20up%20in%20pursuance%20of%20its%20divisive%20politics.%20The%20totality%20of%20the%20problem%20will%20have%20different%20solutions%20and%20different%20laws%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20persecution%20of%20religious%20minorities%20in%20neighbouring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20yet%20another%20tool%20which%20is%20going%20to%20be%20used%20against%20the%20Muslim%20community%20in%20India%2C%20which%20is%20already%20facing%20problems%20like%20hate%20speech%20and%20violence%20against%20them.%20The%20BJP%20has%20constantly%20thrown%20up%20emotive%20and%20divisive%20issues%20to%20strengthen%20its%20electoral%20power%20and%20CAA%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20impact%20in%20that%20context%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20gauge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20good%20that%20many%20chief%20ministers%20like%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20Pinarayi%20Vijayan%20have%20declared%20that%20they%20will%20not%20let%20it%20be%20implemented%20in%20their%20states.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20the%20party%2C%20with%20its%20primary%20goal%20of%20promoting%20divisive%20issues%2C%20has%20to%20be%20combated%20at%20a%20social%20and%20political%20level.%20However%2C%20any%20real%20relief%20on%20this%20front%20will%20only%20come%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20intervenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710860417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F12182004%2FTanushree-Bhasin-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fcaa-one-more-tool-in-bjps-arsenal-against-the-muslim-community%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20was%20truly%20meant%20to%20help%20'persecuted%20Hindus'%2C%20why%20have%20Hindu%20Tamilians%20from%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20persecuted%20groups%2C%20been%20left%20out%20of%20its%20purview%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fcaa-one-more-tool-in-bjps-arsenal-against-the-muslim-community%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bank%20seeks%20to%20recover%20millions%20after%20glitch%20triggers%20massive%20withdrawals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710859560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-ethiopia-commercial_6495095.jpg%3F20240319145032%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fethiopian-bank-seeks-to-recover-millions-after-glitch-triggers-massive-withdrawals-13098142%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ethiopia's%20biggest%20bank%20is%20trying%20to%20recover%20millions%20after%20a%20technical%20glitch%20allowed%20customers%20to%20withdraw%20more%20money%20than%20they%20had%20in%20their%20accounts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fethiop